How to call an API in flutter:

1- Make a Model for the response
2- Make a Repository to call the api
3- Manage your state 



1- Model :
Used to transfer the response form JSON to Dart to be easy to use in our program.

2- Repository:
Used to make the request.

3- State managment:




-- status code :

200 : success , 201 (create)

400: bad request
401: unauthrized
402
403: forbedden
404: Not found
429: to many requests 


500: Server error
501:
502:
503: 




///// state management :
technique to manage our state.
1- separation of consernes
2- enhance the performance

 